{"type":"text","timestamp":1781763397620,"sessionID":"ses_126a3e098ffexlbbiPvr4M06CK","part":{"id":"prt_ed95fc8cd001ThFYjEk3zfVaZo","messageID":"msg_ed95f8fde001fZtCPBffNgu6lj","sessionID":"ses_126a3e098ffexlbbiPvr4M06CK","type":"text","text":"Confirmed a candidate P1: governed scan/ingest applies scope/retention metadata after `indexMemoryFile` commits, but unlike direct `memory_save` it does not wrap that metadata step with rollback/cleanup on failure. I’m re-reading the call sites and direct-save counterpath before recording it.","time":{"start":1781763393741,"end":1781763397617},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0712b7c8379ec2f1016a338d41562c8191b32dfe2ebaffb6b3","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763399885,"sessionID":"ses_126a3e098ffexlbbiPvr4M06CK","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_JKctLXLXMxMeVq19evZMzdTV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts","offset":1038,"limit":20},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1038:       // It does not carry primary-evidence sections or ANCHOR tags by design, so the\n1039:       // strict sufficiency gate would always reject it. Treat constitutional files like\n1040:       // spec docs and pass them through warn-only mode so they index against the same\n1041:       // pipeline without the document-evidence requirements.\n1042:       const isConstitutional = constitutionalSet.has(getCachedKey(filePath));\n1043:       // During force reindex, use warn-only for all files — the goal is to index\n1044:       // everything that has valid frontmatter, not to enforce template contracts on\n1045:       // older files created before current templates were established.\n1046:       const useWarnOnly = force || isSpecDoc || isConstitutional;\n1047:       const indexResult = await indexSingleFile(filePath, force, {\n1048:         ...(useWarnOnly ? { qualityGateMode: 'warn-only' as const } : {}),\n1049:         fromScan: true,\n1050:         asyncEmbedding: true,\n1051:         governance: governedIngest ? governanceDecision : undefined,\n1052:       });\n1053:       processedInScan += 1;\n1054:       ctx.onProgress?.({ processed: processedInScan, total: filesToIndex.length });\n1055:       return indexResult;\n1056:     }, scanBatchSize, undefined, { shouldAbort: () => ctx.isCancelled?.() ?? false });\n1057: \n\n(Showing lines 1038-1057 of 1598. Use offset=1058 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"      // It does not carry primary-evidence sections or ANCHOR tags by design, so the\n      // strict sufficiency gate would always reject it. Treat constitutional files like\n      // spec docs and pass them through warn-only mode so they index against the same\n      // pipeline without the document-evidence requirements.\n      const isConstitutional = constitutionalSet.has(getCachedKey(filePath));\n      // During force reindex, use warn-only for all files — the goal is to index\n      // everything that has valid frontmatter, not to enforce template contracts on\n      // older files created before current templates were established.\n      const useWarnOnly = force || isSpecDoc || isConstitutional;\n      const indexResult = await indexSingleFile(filePath, force, {\n        ...(useWarnOnly ? { qualityGateMode: 'warn-only' as const } : {}),\n        fromScan: true,\n        asyncEmbedding: true,\n        governance: governedIngest ? governanceDecision : undefined,\n      });\n      processedInScan += 1;\n      ctx.onProgress?.({ processed: processedInScan, total: filesToIndex.length });\n      return indexResult;\n    }, scanBatchSize, undefined, { shouldAbort: () => ctx.isCancelled?.() ?? false });\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts","text":"      // It does not carry primary-evidence sections or ANCHOR tags by design, so the\n      // strict sufficiency gate would always reject it. Treat constitutional files like\n      // spec docs and pass them through warn-only mode so they index against the same\n      // pipeline without the document-evidence requirements.\n      const isConstitutional = constitutionalSet.has(getCachedKey(filePath));\n      // During force reindex, use warn-only for all files — the goal is to index\n      // everything that has valid frontmatter, not to enforce template contracts on\n      // older files created before current templates were established.\n      const useWarnOnly = force || isSpecDoc || isConstitutional;\n      const indexResult = await indexSingleFile(filePath, force, {\n        ...(useWarnOnly ? { qualityGateMode: 'warn-only' as const } : {}),\n        fromScan: true,\n        asyncEmbedding: true,\n        governance: governedIngest ? governanceDecision : undefined,\n      });\n      processedInScan += 1;\n      ctx.onProgress?.({ processed: processedInScan, total: filesToIndex.length });\n      return indexResult;\n    }, scanBatchSize, undefined, { shouldAbort: () => ctx.isCancelled?.() ?? false });\n","lineStart":1038,"lineEnd":1057,"totalLines":1598,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts","time":{"start":1781763399875,"end":1781763399882}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0712b7c8379ec2f1016a338d45865481919fed599156e29122"}},"id":"prt_ed95fe0b7001qg2AK0L0a44uk4","sessionID":"ses_126a3e098ffexlbbiPvr4M06CK","messageID":"msg_ed95f8fde001fZtCPBffNgu6lj"}}
